notesStmt.note: Internal colophon: iti śivabhaṭṭasutasatīgarbhajanāgojībhaṭṭakṛte laghuśabdaiṃduśekhare pūrvārddhasamāptim agamat // [saṃvat] 1890 rāmovijapatetarām . . . (f. 364r).

Dated saṃvat 1890 (1837) (f. 364r); the "saṃvat" is not stated in the manuscript, but the work was acquired by the University of Pennsylvania before the possibility of it being the śaka designation, which would make it 1968 A.D., and thus the manuscript must be from 1837 A.D.
Mistakes covered over in yellow or blacked out; some corrections and additions in margins; significant syllables, words, or phrases highlighted in red throughout.

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Manuscript is a grammatical treatise, an arrangement and commentary on the sūtras of the grammarian Pāṇini, along with a parallel commentary by Nāgeśabhaṭṭa, which runs horizontally above and below the main text. Manuscript is incomplete and in three parts, but contains most of the work.
